context:
KR:
&lt;알겠어. 돈키호테… 무슨 일인데 그래?&gt;
EN:
&lt;Okay, Don Quixote. Fine... What is it?&gt;

KR:
&lt;아하, 꼭두새벽에 일어나서 한 쪽 다리 꼬고 신문을 각지게 펼쳐 읽는 그 루틴?&gt;
EN:
&lt;Aha, the newspaper routine. Where he wakes up before the crack of dawn, parks himself on a chair, folds one leg over the other at an exact 90-degree 'figure-four-leg-lock' position, and peruses the morning newspaper?&gt;

KR:
&lt;어, 어… 무슨 소식이 있는데? 신문에 림버스 컴퍼니 소식이라도 나왔어?&gt;
EN:
&lt;Uh... yep, totally. So what's new? What, did an article mention us or something?&gt;

KR:
&lt;진짜?&gt;
EN:
&lt;Wait, really?&gt;

KR:
&lt;그… 그 부분은 빨리 넘기자.&gt;
EN:
&lt;W-well, I don't think we need to hear that part. What else does it say?&gt;

KR:
&lt;돈키호테의 호들갑이 정말 들어맞다니…&gt;
EN:
&lt;No way... Don Quixote wasn't just losing her mind at nothing...?&gt;

KR:
&lt;그러게, 착오가 생겼던 모양이네… 아니면 미리 낸 액수에서 아슬아슬하게 넘겨버렸거나.&gt;
EN:
&lt;Yeah. There must’ve been a minor miscalculation or something. Maybe we fell slightly short of the amount we had to pay?&gt;

KR:
&lt;뭐?!&gt;
EN:
&lt;WHAT?!&gt;

KR:
&lt;아는 거 없어…? 이상, 히스클리프?&gt;
EN:
&lt;Yi Sang? Heathcliff? Know anything about this...?&gt;

KR:
&lt;그럼…&gt;
EN:
&lt;Well, then...&gt;
